-- 6. Calendly vs Loom
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'calendly-vs-loom',
  'saas',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='calendly' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='loom' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Calendly and Loom are two of the most popular async communication tools in the modern workplace, each solving a different piece of the meeting efficiency puzzle. Calendly eliminates scheduling friction by letting contacts book meetings directly based on your real-time availability. Loom reduces the need for meetings altogether by enabling asynchronous video messaging where you can record and share screen recordings with voiceover narration.</p><p>Together, these tools represent a shift toward smarter communication: Calendly ensures that the meetings you do have are booked efficiently, while Loom ensures that many would-be meetings become simple video messages instead. Understanding when to schedule a live meeting versus when to send a Loom video is key to productive team communication.</p><p>This comparison evaluates both platforms on their core capabilities, pricing, integrations, and the specific workflows they optimize to help you decide which tool deserves a place in your tech stack.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Calendly if your primary challenge is scheduling meetings efficiently, whether for sales demos, client consultations, or team syncs. Its booking pages, round-robin routing, and CRM integrations are unmatched. Choose Loom if you want to reduce meetings by communicating asynchronously through video, perfect for project updates, code reviews, and feedback that does not require real-time conversation.</p><p>Most productive teams use both. Calendly for necessary synchronous meetings, Loom for everything that can be handled asynchronously.</p>',
  '<p>Calendly and Loom are complementary tools rather than direct replacements for each other. If evaluating which to adopt first, consider your team''s biggest pain point: too many scheduling back-and-forth emails (Calendly) or too many unnecessary live meetings (Loom). Both offer free plans that make it easy to test before committing to a paid tier.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Sales team booking prospect demos:</strong> Calendly''s automated scheduling with CRM sync eliminates the five-email chain typically needed to book a single demo call.</li><li><strong>Engineering team sharing code reviews:</strong> Loom recordings walking through pull requests save time versus scheduling live review meetings for every PR.</li><li><strong>Consultant managing client intake:</strong> Calendly''s intake forms and payment collection streamline the client booking process from inquiry to paid session.</li><li><strong>Manager providing weekly team updates:</strong> A Loom video summarizing the week replaces a 30-minute all-hands meeting that could have been an email.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Primary function","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Meeting scheduling automation","toolBValue":"Async video messaging","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Free plan","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"1 event type, unlimited bookings","toolBValue":"25 videos, 5-min limit","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Starting price","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$10/user/mo","toolBValue":"$15/user/mo","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Calendar integration","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"Google, Outlook, iCloud, Office 365","toolBValue":"Not applicable","winner":"a"},{"feature":"CRM integration","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"Salesforce, HubSpot native","toolBValue":"Limited CRM integrations","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Video capabilities","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Not applicable","toolBValue":"Screen + cam recording, editing","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Team features","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Round-robin, collective scheduling","toolBValue":"Shared workspace, comments, reactions","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Analytics","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Booking analytics and conversion","toolBValue":"View counts, engagement heatmaps","winner":"tie"}]',
  '[{"question":"Can Loom replace Calendly for scheduling?","answer":"No, Loom does not have scheduling capabilities. It is designed for recording and sharing video messages, not for booking calendar appointments. These tools serve complementary purposes."},{"question":"Can Calendly record meetings like Loom?","answer":"No, Calendly schedules meetings but does not record them. For recording, you would use the video conferencing tool itself (Zoom, Google Meet) or a dedicated tool like Loom for async video."},{"question":"Which tool saves more time for remote teams?","answer":"Both save significant time but in different ways. Studies suggest that async video tools like Loom can reduce meeting time by 30-50%, while scheduling tools like Calendly save an average of 4 hours per week on scheduling logistics."}]',
  'Calendly vs Loom (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Calendly vs Loom compared for workplace productivity. We evaluate scheduling, async video, pricing, and integrations for modern teams.'
);

-- 7. Coda vs Notion
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'coda-vs-notion',
  'saas',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='coda' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='notion' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Coda and Notion are both all-in-one workspace platforms that combine documents, databases, and project management into a single tool. They compete directly for teams looking to consolidate their tool stack into one flexible workspace. However, their approaches differ in meaningful ways that affect daily usability and what is possible to build within each platform.</p><p>Notion has gained massive popularity with its clean, block-based editor and beautiful interface that makes documentation and knowledge management a pleasure. Coda differentiates itself with deeper automation capabilities, powerful formulas that rival spreadsheets, and packs that bring external data directly into your documents. Where Notion feels like a smart wiki with database capabilities, Coda feels more like a programmable document that can replace lightweight apps.</p><p>We compare both platforms across their document editing, database functionality, automation, pricing, and collaboration features to help teams choose the right workspace.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Notion if your team prioritizes beautiful documentation, knowledge management, and a wiki-like experience with linked databases. Its design-forward approach and extensive template gallery make it the fastest path to an organized team workspace. Choose Coda if you need more powerful automation, deeper formula capabilities, and the ability to build interactive mini-apps within your documents without code.</p><p>For documentation and knowledge bases, Notion is the stronger choice. For teams that need document-powered workflows and automations, Coda offers more flexibility.</p>',
  '<p>Migrating between Coda and Notion requires manual effort since neither offers a direct import tool for the other. Both support Markdown import and export, which covers basic text content. Database structures, formulas, and automations will need to be rebuilt manually. For small workspaces, migration takes a few days. For large team wikis with hundreds of pages, plan for one to two weeks of gradual transfer.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Product team building a wiki:</strong> Notion''s clean block editor, nested pages, and linked databases create an intuitive knowledge base that product teams love.</li><li><strong>Operations team automating workflows:</strong> Coda''s automations, buttons, and packs let ops teams build interactive approval workflows and status dashboards without code.</li><li><strong>Startup documenting processes:</strong> Notion''s extensive template gallery and simple onboarding get startups organized quickly with minimal setup time.</li><li><strong>Finance team building dynamic reports:</strong> Coda''s spreadsheet-grade formulas and cross-doc data pulling create living reports that update automatically from external sources.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Document editor","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Powerful with formula support","toolBValue":"Beautiful block-based editor","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Database capabilities","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Tables with deep formulas","toolBValue":"Linked databases with relations","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Automation","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Built-in rules and automations","toolBValue":"Basic automations on paid plans","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Free plan","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"Generous for individuals","toolBValue":"Generous for individuals","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Starting price","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$10/user/mo (Team)","toolBValue":"$10/user/mo (Plus)","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Templates","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Gallery of templates","toolBValue":"Massive template gallery","winner":"b"},{"feature":"API and integrations","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"Packs for live external data","toolBValue":"API and 100+ integrations","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Mobile experience","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Functional mobile app","toolBValue":"Excellent mobile app","winner":"b"}]',
  '[{"question":"Is Coda more powerful than Notion for automations?","answer":"Yes, Coda''s automation engine is significantly more capable. It supports complex conditional logic, scheduled automations, and buttons that trigger multi-step workflows, while Notion''s automations are more basic."},{"question":"Which tool has better documentation features?","answer":"Notion is generally considered superior for pure documentation and knowledge management thanks to its clean editor, beautiful typography, and intuitive page nesting that makes building a team wiki effortless."},{"question":"Can either tool replace a spreadsheet?","answer":"Coda comes closer to replacing spreadsheets with its formula language that supports IF statements, lookups, and calculations similar to Excel. Notion''s formula capabilities are more limited but sufficient for basic calculations."}]',
  'Coda vs Notion (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Coda vs Notion workspace platforms compared. We evaluate documents, databases, automation, pricing, and collaboration to help you choose.'
);

-- 8. Basecamp vs ClickUp
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'basecamp-vs-clickup',
  'saas',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='basecamp' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='clickup' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Basecamp and ClickUp represent two opposite philosophies in project management software. Basecamp champions simplicity and opinionated design, deliberately limiting features to keep teams focused on communication and task completion without overwhelm. ClickUp embraces maximalism, offering an enormous feature set that aims to be the one app to replace them all, from tasks and docs to whiteboards and chat.</p><p>This philosophical divide makes the choice deeply personal. Teams frustrated by tool complexity find Basecamp''s calm, focused approach refreshing. Teams that want every possible feature in one place gravitate toward ClickUp''s ambitious all-in-one platform. Neither approach is universally better, but one will almost certainly fit your team''s culture more naturally.</p><p>We compare pricing, features, usability, and team workflows to help you decide between Basecamp''s disciplined simplicity and ClickUp''s feature-rich flexibility.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Basecamp if your team values simplicity, clear communication, and a tool that does not require weeks of configuration. Its flat pricing model is especially attractive for larger teams since you pay per account, not per user. Choose ClickUp if your team needs advanced project management features like Gantt charts, time tracking, custom fields, goals, and multiple view types within a single platform.</p><p>Basecamp wins on simplicity and pricing predictability. ClickUp wins on feature depth and customization. Consider your team''s tolerance for complexity when deciding.</p>',
  '<p>ClickUp offers a Basecamp import feature that maps projects to Spaces, to-do lists to task lists, and messages to comments. The migration is relatively smooth for task data but you will need to rebuild any workflows that rely on Basecamp''s specific communication tools like Campfires and Message Boards. If moving from ClickUp to Basecamp, expect to simplify your workflow significantly since many ClickUp features have no Basecamp equivalent.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Creative agency with 50+ people:</strong> Basecamp''s flat pricing and simple interface keep agency teams focused on client work without per-seat cost anxiety.</li><li><strong>Software development team running sprints:</strong> ClickUp''s sprint management, Git integration, custom statuses, and automation handle complex dev workflows effectively.</li><li><strong>Small business managing multiple projects:</strong> Basecamp''s project-centric organization with built-in messaging keeps small teams aligned without feature overwhelm.</li><li><strong>Marketing team with complex campaign workflows:</strong> ClickUp''s custom fields, dependencies, Gantt charts, and dashboards track multi-stage campaigns with precision.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Pricing model","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$299/mo flat (unlimited users)","toolBValue":"$7/user/mo and up","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Free plan","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"No free plan","toolBValue":"Generous free forever plan","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Ease of use","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Intentionally simple","toolBValue":"Powerful but complex","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Task views","category":"Core","toolAValue":"List and Kanban only","toolBValue":"15+ views (list, board, Gantt, etc.)","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Built-in communication","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Message boards, campfires, pings","toolBValue":"Chat, comments, email integration","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Time tracking","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Not built-in","toolBValue":"Native time tracking","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Custom fields","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Not available","toolBValue":"Extensive custom fields","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Mobile app","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Clean, fast mobile app","toolBValue":"Feature-rich mobile app","winner":"tie"}]',
  '[{"question":"Is Basecamp''s flat pricing actually cheaper than ClickUp?","answer":"For teams over 40 users, Basecamp''s $299/month flat rate is significantly cheaper than ClickUp''s per-user pricing. For small teams under 10, ClickUp''s free plan or lower per-user cost may be more economical."},{"question":"Can ClickUp be simplified to work like Basecamp?","answer":"You can strip down ClickUp by disabling features and using simple list views, but its core design emphasizes options and customization. If you truly want simplicity, Basecamp''s opinionated approach delivers it more naturally."},{"question":"Which tool is better for remote teams?","answer":"Both work well for remote teams. Basecamp''s built-in message boards and check-in questions are purpose-built for async remote work. ClickUp offers more real-time collaboration features like whiteboards and docs."}]',
  'Basecamp vs ClickUp (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Basecamp vs ClickUp compared for project management. We evaluate simplicity vs features, pricing models, and team workflows.'
);

-- 9. Confluence vs Notion
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'confluence-vs-notion',
  'saas',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='confluence' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='notion' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Confluence and Notion are the two most prominent team knowledge management platforms, each commanding massive user bases but serving different organizational cultures. Confluence, built by Atlassian, is the established enterprise wiki that integrates deeply with Jira, Trello, and the broader Atlassian ecosystem. Notion is the modern upstart that has redefined what a workspace tool can be with its flexible block-based approach to documents and databases.</p><p>The generational divide between these tools is apparent immediately. Confluence carries the weight of enterprise features like granular permissions, compliance controls, and deep Jira integration that large organizations depend on. Notion offers a fresh, intuitive experience that makes creating and organizing knowledge feel almost enjoyable, attracting startups and modern teams who value design and flexibility.</p><p>We compare these knowledge platforms on documentation, collaboration, integrations, pricing, and the organizational contexts where each excels.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Confluence if your organization relies on the Atlassian ecosystem, needs enterprise-grade permissions and compliance features, or has established documentation workflows that depend on structured spaces and page trees. Choose Notion if you want a more modern, flexible workspace that combines documentation with databases, task management, and a design-forward experience your team will actually enjoy using.</p><p>For Atlassian shops and enterprises, Confluence integrates seamlessly. For modern teams seeking a unified workspace, Notion delivers a superior experience.</p>',
  '<p>Notion offers a Confluence import tool that transfers pages and basic formatting. However, Confluence macros, advanced formatting, and Jira-linked content require manual recreation. For large Confluence instances with thousands of pages, plan for a phased migration over several weeks. Going from Notion to Confluence, you will need to export as Markdown and import, losing database views and linked databases.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Enterprise engineering org using Jira:</strong> Confluence''s native Jira integration embeds live issue data, sprint reports, and roadmaps directly in documentation pages.</li><li><strong>Startup building its first knowledge base:</strong> Notion''s intuitive editor and templates let small teams build a beautiful, organized wiki in hours rather than days.</li><li><strong>Regulated industry needing compliance:</strong> Confluence''s granular space permissions, audit logs, and Atlassian Guard integration meet strict compliance requirements.</li><li><strong>Product team combining docs with project tracking:</strong> Notion''s linked databases connect documentation pages to task boards, creating a unified product management workspace.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Editor experience","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Traditional rich text with macros","toolBValue":"Modern block-based editor","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Free plan","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"Up to 10 users","toolBValue":"Unlimited members (limited blocks)","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Starting price","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$6.05/user/mo","toolBValue":"$10/user/mo","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Jira integration","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"Deep native integration","toolBValue":"Basic third-party integration","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Database capabilities","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Limited to tables","toolBValue":"Full relational databases","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Enterprise permissions","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Granular space and page permissions","toolBValue":"Basic workspace permissions","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Template ecosystem","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Marketplace templates","toolBValue":"Extensive built-in template gallery","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Search quality","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Full-text with CQL queries","toolBValue":"Fast, intuitive search","winner":"tie"}]',
  '[{"question":"Can Notion replace Confluence for enterprises?","answer":"For smaller enterprises and modern organizations, yes. However, large enterprises with deep Atlassian ecosystem dependencies, strict compliance needs, and thousands of existing Confluence pages may find the migration challenging."},{"question":"Is Confluence''s editor as modern as Notion?","answer":"Confluence has modernized significantly with its cloud editor, but Notion''s block-based approach still feels more intuitive and flexible for most users. Confluence compensates with powerful macros for structured content."},{"question":"Which tool is better for technical documentation?","answer":"Both handle technical docs well. Confluence excels with its code macros, Jira integration, and structured page hierarchies. Notion offers a cleaner editing experience with code blocks and the ability to embed databases alongside documentation."}]',
  'Confluence vs Notion (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Confluence vs Notion compared for team knowledge management. We evaluate editing, integrations, pricing, and enterprise features.'
);

-- 10. Freshservice vs Freshdesk
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'freshservice-vs-freshdesk',
  'saas',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='freshservice' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='freshdesk' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Freshservice and Freshdesk are both products from Freshworks, but they serve fundamentally different audiences and use cases. Freshdesk is an external customer support platform designed to help businesses manage customer inquiries across email, chat, phone, and social media. Freshservice is an internal IT service management (ITSM) platform built for IT teams to handle employee requests, manage IT assets, and run IT operations following ITIL best practices.</p><p>The confusion between these products is common because they share similar interfaces and come from the same company. However, their feature sets are tailored for completely different scenarios. Freshdesk focuses on customer satisfaction, ticket resolution speed, and multi-channel support. Freshservice focuses on incident management, change management, asset tracking, and IT workflow automation.</p><p>This comparison clarifies the differences, helping you choose the right Freshworks product for your organization''s specific needs.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Freshdesk if you need to support external customers with a multi-channel helpdesk that handles email, chat, phone, and social media support tickets. Choose Freshservice if your IT team needs an ITSM platform for managing internal employee requests, IT assets, changes, and incidents following ITIL frameworks.</p><p>Many organizations use both products: Freshdesk for customer-facing support and Freshservice for internal IT operations. They integrate natively within the Freshworks ecosystem.</p>',
  '<p>Since both are Freshworks products, they share login credentials and administrative interfaces. Running both simultaneously is common and supported natively. If you are currently using Freshdesk for internal IT support, migrating tickets and configurations to Freshservice can be done with Freshworks'' built-in migration tools and support team assistance. The transition typically takes one to two weeks.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>IT department handling employee requests:</strong> Freshservice''s service catalog, automated workflows, and ITIL-aligned processes handle employee IT needs professionally.</li><li><strong>E-commerce company supporting customers:</strong> Freshdesk''s multi-channel ticketing, satisfaction surveys, and knowledge base manage high-volume customer inquiries efficiently.</li><li><strong>Enterprise managing IT assets:</strong> Freshservice''s asset discovery, CMDB, and lifecycle management track hardware and software across the organization.</li><li><strong>SaaS company providing product support:</strong> Freshdesk''s product forums, canned responses, and Freddy AI bot resolve common product questions automatically.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Primary audience","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Internal IT teams","toolBValue":"External customer support","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"ITIL compliance","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Full ITIL support","toolBValue":"Not designed for ITIL","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Asset management","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Full CMDB and asset tracking","toolBValue":"Not available","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Multi-channel support","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Email and portal","toolBValue":"Email, chat, phone, social","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Starting price","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$19/agent/mo","toolBValue":"Free (up to 10 agents)","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Knowledge base","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Internal IT knowledge base","toolBValue":"Customer-facing knowledge base","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Change management","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Built-in change workflows","toolBValue":"Not available","winner":"a"},{"feature":"AI capabilities","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Freddy AI for IT","toolBValue":"Freddy AI for support","winner":"tie"}]',
  '[{"question":"Can Freshdesk be used for internal IT support?","answer":"While technically possible, Freshdesk lacks ITSM-specific features like asset management, change management, and ITIL workflows. Freshservice is purpose-built for these internal IT needs and is the recommended choice."},{"question":"Can I use both Freshservice and Freshdesk together?","answer":"Yes, many organizations use both products simultaneously. Freshservice handles internal IT operations while Freshdesk manages external customer support. They integrate natively as part of the Freshworks ecosystem."},{"question":"Which product is more affordable?","answer":"Freshdesk offers a free plan for up to 10 agents, making it cheaper to start. Freshservice starts at $19 per agent per month with no free tier. However, Freshservice''s IT-specific features eliminate the need for separate asset management and ITSM tools."}]',
  'Freshservice vs Freshdesk (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Freshservice vs Freshdesk compared from the Freshworks suite. We clarify IT service management vs customer support features and pricing.'
);

